What is gaze-based interaction?
Interacting with objects by looking at them, using the userâ€™s gaze direction instead of a controller or mouse.

Why is dwell time useful?
It allows selection or activation by looking at an object for a set duration, reducing the need for physical input.

How does sensory feedback improve realism?
Visual, audio, or haptic feedback makes interactions feel more responsive and natural.

Which cube felt most immersive and why?
The cube with gaze interaction and feedback felt most immersive because it reacted immediately to where the user looked.
